The definitions and values of parameters of (1) can be found in Table A4 in Additional file 1. The daily force of infection was considered to accumulate. However, it was assumed that if a susceptible does not gather any additional force of infection (i.e., does not come in contact with any infected) for two consecutive days, the cumulative force of infection for the susceptible reduces to zero. At the end of each day, the cumulative value of λi was used to calculate the probability of infection for susceptible i as  \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
